description.author: Anton Ekblad <anton@ekblad.cc>
description.description:
This package provides a featureful compiler from Haskell to
Javascript. It generates small, fast code, makes use of
standard Haskell libraries, integrates with Cabal, supports
most GHC extensions and works on Windows, Linux and OSX.
Bug reports are highly appreciated.

package-flags.name: portable
package-flags.description:
Install Haste into a self-contained directory. Package databases are
still local to each user. Primarily useful for global installs.

package-flags.name: static
package-flags.description:
Build a statically linked binary. Only really useful together with
portable.

package-flags.name: only-library
package-flags.description:
Only install the Haste server-side libraries; no binaries.
This is useful if you installed pre-built binaries but still want
to use Haste with vanilla GHC, for Haste.App for instance.
